{"clientId":"67781","type":"MessageNotification","name":"Chat","data":{"from":"31323334353637383930313233343536:47562b2770187dd8d00a8aebf2cee48e","to":"31323334353637383930313233343536:4d4a0759c90685ef504d84dea921b370","message":"dsds","chatMessageType":"Text","date":1742504371239},"_id":"7LQAS59SXmcFzt8T"}
{"clientId":"bot_74298","type":"MessageNotification","name":"Chat","data":{"from":"31323334353637383930313233343536:cee87909e7359985b3250f87e3360eb0","to":"31323334353637383930313233343536:2ff52ef52e56036e82199f8c3ddc813d","message":"Abu Dhabi is the capital of the United Arab Emirates and is known for its rich cultural heritage, rapid modernization, and unparalleled economic growth. The city is situated along the coast of the Arabian Gulf and is the largest of the seven emirates. Abu Dhabi is a blend of tradition and innovation, where ancient customs coexist with cutting-edge technology. The city is a global hub for business, tourism, and culture, with world-class infrastructure, luxury developments, and a thriving economy driven by oil, real estate, and diverse sectors. Abu Dhabi is also deeply connected to its Arab roots, with traditional markets, desert landscapes, and historic forts offering a glimpse into the Emirati way of life. The city is home to numerous international companies and institutions, and its government continues to invest in education, healthcare, and technology to shape a prosperous future for all its residents.","chatMessageType":"Text","date":1742165574469},"_id":"7a1O2mLqqTlgGmEg"}
{"clientId":"bot_55389","type":"MessageNotification","name":"Chat","data":{"from":"31323334353637383930313233343536:13a402f55c5598575ac91b5fdc621ac6","to":"31323334353637383930313233343536:d0a00e49305c0b081e75997d3326eafb","message":"Hello! How can I help you today?","chatMessageType":"Text","date":1738531794093},"_id":"7bbvzAQTOE3XDHhq"}
{"clientId":"bot_55389","type":"MessageNotification","name":"Chat","data":{"from":"31323334353637383930313233343536:13a402f55c5598575ac91b5fdc621ac6","to":"31323334353637383930313233343536:d0a00e49305c0b081e75997d3326eafb","message":"context: 'The Sharjah International Book Fair (SIBF) was established by H.H. Sheikh Dr. Sultan Bin Mohammed Al Qasimi, a Member of the Supreme Council and the Ruler of Sharjah. He founded it in 1982 to bring to life his vision of creating a nation of readers. The rich legacy of the SIBF has extended across four decades. It promotes both cultural and intellectual growth and exchange worldwide. The Sharjah International Book Fair has crossed 50 million in sales. Its a 12day cultural and literary event where book lovers can browse through millions of books and buy them at great prices. The fair also connects authors and publishers from all over the globe and facilitates meetings to discuss current trends and potential opportunities to work together. In 2023 15 million books displayed 2,023 publishers 109 participating countries 1500 childrens activities SIBF has expanded its reach beyond the boundaries of Sharjah. The platform heartily welcomes every speaker and author to interact. The international presence of SIBF has allowed it to explore different literary traditions and perspectives. Today, SIBF is the thirdlargest book fair in the world. It is the most prestigious event in the Arab world and a hub for the most exciting literary events in the region. Every year, SIBF attracts the finest global talent in publishing and related industries to the Middle East. Sharjah International Book Fair has been awarded membership to various international organizations such as the AfroAsian Publishers Association and GCC Book Committee and has been recognized by the International Publishers Association. In a dynamic environment that converges various voices in one place, SIBF offers various opportunities, captivating events, and activities such as author signings, noteworthy panel discussions, knowledgeable workshops, and exhibition sessions. SIBF has also initiated various paths for its readers. These include educational initiatives, the Publishers Conference, Emirati Book Awards (Emirati Novel Award, Best Emirati Creative Literature Book, Best Emirati Academic Book, and Best Emirati First Novel Award), Best Arabic Novel Award, and Best International Book Awards (Best International NonFiction book, Best International Fiction book, and Best International First Novel Award). These initiatives have inspired many learners and led to innovation in publishing and related industries. Sharjah International Book Fair has been recognized by various international organizations and has been awarded membership to several prestigious organizations, such as the AfroAsian Publishers Association and the GCC Book Committee. The fair has also been recognized by the International Publishers Association, and it has been a driving force behind the development of the Sharjah Literary Scene.'","chatMessageType":"Text","date":1738852065468},"_id":"7vTB49NrtywtCjxK"}
