{"clientId":"bot_54701","type":"MessageNotification","name":"Chat","data":{"from":"31323334353637383930313233343536:1222827d9784c14eb902377528ec606b","to":"31323334353637383930313233343536:d0a00e49305c0b081e75997d3326eafb","message":"Here's a simple HTML card with an image in the center:\n\n```html\n<card>\n  <div class=\"card-header\">\n    <h2 class=\"card-title\">Card Title</h2>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"card-body\">\n    <img src=\"image.jpg\" alt=\"Image\">\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"card-footer\">\n    <button class=\"btn btn-primary\">Save Card</button>\n  </div>\n</card>\n```\n\nThis card has a header, a body with an image, and a footer with a save button. You can customize the image and the button to fit your needs.\n\nIf you want to add more content to the card, you can use the `<div>` tags to create additional sections. For example:\n\n```html\n<card>\n  <div class=\"card-header\">\n    <h2 class=\"card-title\">Card Title</h2>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"card-body\">\n    <h3>Card Content</h3>\n    <p>This is some content.</p>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"card-footer\">\n    <button class=\"btn btn-primary\">Save Card</button>\n  </div>\n</card>\n```\n\nYou can also use the `<div>` tags to create a table or a list. For example:\n\n```html\n<card>\n  <div class=\"card-header\">\n    <h2 class=\"card-title\">Card Title</h2>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"card-body\">\n    <table>\n      <thead>\n        <tr>\n          <th>Column 1</th>\n          <th>Column 2</th>\n        </tr>\n      </thead>\n      <tbody>\n        <tr>\n          <td>Column 1</td>\n          <td>Column 2</td>\n        </tr>\n      </tbody>\n    </table>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"card-footer\">\n    <button class=\"btn btn-primary\">Save Card</button>\n  </div>\n</card>\n```\n\nThis will create a table with two columns, and a list with two items. You can customize the table and list to fit your needs.","chatMessageType":"Text","date":1739197332030},"_id":"EROT19NpYKyXvtPl"}
