{"clientId":"bot_44772","type":"MessageNotification","name":"Chat","data":{"from":"31323334353637383930313233343536:05fba74b47bedbb984e1a8583b06a5d3","to":"31323334353637383930313233343536:2ff52ef52e56036e82199f8c3ddc813d","message":"context: 'JavaScript is a programming language that is used to create web applications. It is a client-side scripting language that allows developers to create interactive web pages and web applications. JavaScript is widely used by developers to create web applications, including web pages, web applications, and mobile apps. You can use JavaScript to create interactive web pages, web applications, and even mobile apps. JavaScript is available on npm and is widely used by developers.'","chatMessageType":"Text","date":1741632410136},"_id":"Qde6EQH4dHKXdClv"}
{"clientId":"bot_74298","type":"MessageNotification","name":"Chat","data":{"from":"31323334353637383930313233343536:cee87909e7359985b3250f87e3360eb0","to":"31323334353637383930313233343536:2ff52ef52e56036e82199f8c3ddc813d","message":"The Department of Government Enablement (DGE) in Abu Dhabi, United Arab Emirates, is committed to several key initiatives that aim to enhance public services, support government entities, citizens, and residents. Here are some of the main initiatives:\n\n1. GovTalent: This initiative focuses on developing leadership skills and establishing productive work environments within Abu Dhabis government departments. It aims to equip employees with the necessary skills to meet the evolving needs of the community.\n\n2. GovAcademy: This program offers training and development opportunities to government employees, aiming to enhance their skills and knowledge. It supports the growth of public sector employees and helps them adapt to the changing needs of the community.\n\n3. GovProcurement: This initiative aims to optimize procurement processes within Abu Dhabis government entities, ensuring that public sector employees are equipped to meet the demands of the local economy. It provides agile frameworks, robust processes, and a strong digital foundation.\n\n4. TAMM: The unified omnichannel government ecosystem offered by the DGE provides a wide range of services provided by the Government of Abu Dhabi. It combines human interaction with technology-led solutions across various channels and facilities, aiming to deliver seamless and efficient public services.\n\n5. Mawaheb: Recognized as the first employment support center in Abu Dhabi, Mawaheb is career-driven and responsive to the needs of employers. It prepares job seekers for current and future opportunities in the UAEs labor market.\n\n6. TAMM: The TAMM platform is a key component of the DGE's initiatives, offering a wide range of services provided by the Government of Abu Dhabi. It combines human interaction with technology-led solutions across various channels and facilities, aiming to deliver seamless and efficient public services.\n\n7. Mawaheb: The TAMM platform is also used by Mawaheb, the first employment support center in Abu Dhabi, to provide career guidance and support to job seekers.\n\nThese initiatives are designed to enhance the quality of life for Abu Dhabis citizens, support the growth of the local economy, and ensure that public sector employees are equipped to meet the evolving needs of the community.","chatMessageType":"Text","date":1742166112633},"_id":"Qj4DwMInBEYMKvzF"}
{"clientId":"bot_55389","type":"MessageNotification","name":"Chat","data":{"from":"31323334353637383930313233343536:13a402f55c5598575ac91b5fdc621ac6","to":"31323334353637383930313233343536:d0a00e49305c0b081e75997d3326eafb","message":"The Sharjah International Book Fair (SIBF) was established in 1982 by H.H. Sheikh Dr. Sultan Bin Mohammed Al Qasimi, a Member of the Supreme Council and the Ruler of Sharjah.","chatMessageType":"Text","date":1738533448658},"_id":"R1qaXf4LQ18J28a5"}
