{"clientId":"bot_54701","type":"MessageNotification","name":"Chat","data":{"from":"31323334353637383930313233343536:1222827d9784c14eb902377528ec606b","to":"31323334353637383930313233343536:d0a00e49305c0b081e75997d3326eafb","message":"Yes, Liferay is an open-source digital experience platform (DXP). This means that the source code of Liferay is freely available for anyone to study, modify, and distribute under the terms of the GNU General Public License version 3 (GPLv3).\n\nThe open-source nature of Liferay allows it to be developed and maintained by a diverse group of contributors, contributing to its growth and evolution over time. This collaborative approach fosters innovation and ensures that Liferay continues to evolve with new technologies and business needs.\n\nBy choosing Liferay, you have access to a robust ecosystem of tools, libraries, and frameworks that enable you to build custom digital experiences tailored to your organization’s unique requirements. Whether you're developing a website, intranet, or self-service portal, Liferay provides the necessary tools and capabilities to achieve your goals effectively.","chatMessageType":"Text","date":1738743333092},"_id":"W6CVTp6nM7WlYuSr"}
