{"clientId":"bot_55389","type":"MessageNotification","name":"Chat","data":{"from":"31323334353637383930313233343536:13a402f55c5598575ac91b5fdc621ac6","to":"31323334353637383930313233343536:d0a00e49305c0b081e75997d3326eafb","message":"SIBF stands for \"Sharjah International Book Fair\" and it's an annual event held in Sharjah, United Arab Emirates. Established in 1982 by H.H. Sheikh Dr. Sultan Bin Mohammed Al Qasimi, the event aims to promote cultural and intellectual growth globally.\n\nThe Sharjah International Book Fair covers four decades since its inception, making it one of the oldest book fairs in the world. Over 50 million books were sold during the fair's 12-day run, showcasing a wide range of titles from around the globe.\n\nKey features of the Sharjah International Book Fair include:\n\n1. Cultural and Literary Exchange: It brings together authors, publishers, and other professionals from various parts of the world.\n2. International Presence: The fair attracts speakers, authors, and industry experts from multiple countries.\n3. Educational Initiatives: It hosts various programs aimed at promoting literacy and education among young people.\n4. Exhibitions: The fair features a diverse array of books, including fiction, non-fiction, poetry, and more.\n5. Author Signings: Many prominent authors participate in signing ceremonies, allowing fans to meet and purchase their works.\n6. Panels and Workshops: There are numerous forums where experts share insights on current trends and future possibilities in the publishing industry.\n7. Exhibition Sessions: Participants can showcase their creations in exhibitions, providing a platform for creativity and innovation.\n\nThe Sharjah International Book Fair plays a crucial role in shaping the literary landscape of the Middle East and beyond, fostering collaboration between authors, publishers, and industry professionals.","chatMessageType":"Text","date":1738848223036},"_id":"eOnb9CYncGFJPzyV"}
