{"clientId":"bot_74298","type":"MessageNotification","name":"Chat","data":{"from":"31323334353637383930313233343536:cee87909e7359985b3250f87e3360eb0","to":"31323334353637383930313233343536:2ff52ef52e56036e82199f8c3ddc813d","message":"The Department of Government Enablement (DGE) is a centralized government entity in Abu Dhabi, United Arab Emirates, dedicated to enhancing public services and supporting government entities, citizens, and residents. It is a key player in Abu Dhabis efforts to align with its growth strategy and provide efficient, effective, and innovative public services. The DGE focuses on several key initiatives, including GovTalent, GovAcademy, GovProcurement, and TAMM, among others. These initiatives aim to develop leadership skills, improve work environments, optimize procurement processes, and provide a unified and integrated government ecosystem. The DGE plays a crucial role in Abu Dhabis public sector, striving to enhance the quality of life for its residents through innovative and efficient government services.","chatMessageType":"Text","date":1742284605195},"_id":"r6tfxABTF33RM7il"}
