{"clientId":"bot_55389","type":"MessageNotification","name":"Chat","data":{"from":"31323334353637383930313233343536:d0a00e49305c0b081e75997d3326eafb","to":"31323334353637383930313233343536:13a402f55c5598575ac91b5fdc621ac6","message":"hello","chatMessageType":"Text","date":1738530785016},"_id":"vW1zPjknLwwhNLx7"}
{"clientId":"bot_54701","type":"MessageNotification","name":"Chat","data":{"from":"31323334353637383930313233343536:1222827d9784c14eb902377528ec606b","to":"31323334353637383930313233343536:d0a00e49305c0b081e75997d3326eafb","message":"Sure! Here's an example of an HTML page with a blue button:\n\n```html\n<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n    <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\n    <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\">\n    <title>Blue Button</title>\n    <style>\n        body {\n            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\n            background-color: #f0f0f0;\n            color: #333;\n            margin: 0;\n            padding: 0;\n        }\n        .container {\n            display: flex;\n            justify-content: center;\n            align-items: center;\n            height: 100vh;\n            background-color: #fff;\n            box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);\n        }\n        .button {\n            padding: 10px 20px;\n            font-size: 16px;\n            cursor: pointer;\n            border: none;\n            border-radius: 5px;\n            background-color: #007BFF;\n            color: white;\n            transition: background-color 0.3s ease;\n        }\n        .button:hover {\n            background-color: #0056b3;\n        }\n    </style>\n</head>\n<body>\n    <div class=\"container\">\n        <button class=\"button\">Click Me!</button>\n    </div>\n</body>\n</html>\n```\n\n### Explanation:\n- **HTML (`index.html`)**:\n  - The `div` element with the class `container` acts as the main container for the button.\n  - Inside the container, there's a `button` element with the class `button`.\n  - The button has a blue background color (`#007BFF`) and white text color (`#FFFFFF`).\n  - It also has a hover effect when clicked (`background-color: #0056b3;`).\n\n- **CSS (`styles.css`)**:\n  - The `.container` class centers the button within the container.\n  - The `.button` class styles the button itself, including padding, font size, and other properties.\n  - The `.button:hover` class applies a different background color when the button is hovered over.\n\nThis HTML and CSS code will create a simple blue button with a hover effect.","chatMessageType":"Text","date":1739199206413},"_id":"vft3KfmpEM8fuqAJ"}
